# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY — required, server-side. Used to fetch a video's comments.
#
# This is the ONLY secret the server needs. Your LLM provider key (Groq, Gemini,
# OpenAI, Anthropic) is entered in the app UI at runtime, NOT here.
#
# How to get it:
#   1. https://console.cloud.google.com/  →  create/select a project
#   2. Enable the API:
#      https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/youtube.googleapis.com
#   3. Create the key:
#      https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials  →  Create credentials
#      →  API key
#
# IMPORTANT — avoid the common mistake:
#   • The key MUST look like  AIzaSy...  (a plain Google Cloud API key).
#   • Do NOT tick "Authenticate API calls through a service account" when
#     creating it. That produces an "AQ...." token, and YouTube rejects it with:
#       401  "API keys are not supported by this API. Expected OAuth2 access token"
#   • Application restrictions: leave as "None" (server-side fetch sends no
#     referrer). API restrictions: "YouTube Data API v3" is fine.
#
# After editing this file, RESTART the dev server — env is read only at startup.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=AIzaSy...
